section.text:
That the Secretary of Health and Human Services has failed to meet the requirement of Article II, section 3, clause 5, of the Constitution of the United States to take care that a law be faithfully executed, with respect to the policy of the Department of Health and Human Services providing for the authorization, approval, renewal, modification, or extension of any experimental, pilot, or demonstration project under 
          section 1115 of the Social Security Act (
          42 U.S.C. 1315
        ) that waives compliance with a requirement of 
          section 407 of such Act (
          42 U.S.C. 607
        ) through a waiver of 
          section 402 of such Act (
          42 U.S.C. 602
        ); and that the House of Representatives shall bring a civil action in the United States District Court for the District of Columbia for declaratory or injunctive relief to challenge the policy of the Secretary of Health and Human Services.
